<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The call memset(&ts_end, 0, sizeof(ts_end)); is executed in the else branch when msecs <= 0, but ts_end is only read later in the function when msecs > 0. For the executed case (msecs <= 0) ts_end is never used, so removing the memset would not affect program behaviour. This constitutes dead code (an executed operation whose removal would not change program behaviour).
</scenario>
